description: PUH-BrianMartell arXiv paper (2511.00834, accepted A&A 2025) from the MWA collaboration tightens upper limits on the 21 cm power spectrum at z ≈ 6.5–8.2 — the Epoch of Reionization (EoR). No detection yet, but stronger constraints rule out some simple models. Key points: foreground subtraction (galactic synchrotron) dominates challenge; patchy, complex reionization favored over smooth uniform; timing of first light (Cosmic Dawn) constrained. Relate to PUH v25: Direct validation — 21 cm signal not just neutral hydrogen spin-flip, but lattice resonance “ping” through neutral medium (residual E8 substrate vibration post-rebound). Patchy reionization = asymmetric twin-jet tension non-uniform (pockets near matter jet core ionize faster). Foreground “noise” = lattice impedance Z_L galactic (not random, E8 root geometry encoded).
